
=Bio=

(Raffael Kemenczy) 

My main interest lies with unlocking humanity's potential and ensuring the highest possible quality of life for everyone. I consider personal empowerment and the establishment of distributed peer-to-peer structures in all areas of life as paramount. Realising spiritual truths such as consciousness as prime agent and all-oneness (acintya bhedabheda-tattva) puts a different framing to these views and (the perception of) reality as a whole.

I talk on the interconnections between communication, economy, psychology, society and power structures as well as concepts of sustainability, world-views and spirituality. Recent essays and activities can be found via my website below - please feel free to contact me.


([http://p2pfoundation.net/Project_Starfish Project Starfish] deals with the establishment of a world-wide user-controlled network based on a distributed architecture, its possible social opportunities and implications as well as its technological feasibility.)

